HEADWORD: Nerved
<hw>Nerved</hw> <pr>(n⟦etil⟧rvd)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having nerves of a special character; <as>as,
weak-<ex>nerved</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having nerves, or simple and
parallel ribs or veins.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nerveless</ent>⟦br⟧
